<subSubSection id="9F8C5265E151268DEAC8258C6A5319EB" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph id="E50757EB17F10E7C8091F0C3B94BB63F" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="85F449D6F09CAB5CD8B7E7B7B50C401D" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis id="F96632C0216750F67B9AC491AF733971" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Pereira Neto et al.</emphasis>
234 (RB), from Mun. Patrocinio in Minas Gerais, is atypically densely tomentose and distant from the main population and may represent a distinct species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0848560BE60B82F6FEC9D36D75F7F514" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<taxonomicName id="72C2DB2B1C3BA8189416A6C8446ECB65" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Calystegia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="discolor">
<emphasis id="6D16E981AC37755C704995D1F937424A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Calystegia discolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is included in this synonomy with some doubt. The extant isotypes are of poor quality and do not show the distinct inflorescence of 
<taxonomicName id="81C03651BEA67E66BD2A1273F9F0C03B" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="marcellia">
<emphasis id="D5D21F4E608AEC7339FFFA5DD5706C5E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ipomoea marcellia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The type was collected in Minas Gerais and may correspond to the form represented by 
<emphasis id="C5DFBDA98AF77D81EB989A3FDC2730AA" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Pereira Neto et al.</emphasis>
234.
</paragraph>
